{
  "texts": [
    "For the entanglement entropy (EE) of the boundary MPS, as reported in the main text, we obtain the reduced density matrix ρ from the fixed-point CTMs (see Fig. 6).",
    "The EE is then given by:S = - i λ i log λ i,(9)where λ i are the eigenvalues of ρ.",
    "To compute the correlation length from the fixed-point boundary MPS, we first construct the transfer matrix T (see Fig. 6) in either the horizontal or vertical direction using the MPS tensors.",
    "The correlation length ξ (along the corresponding direction) is then given by:ξ = - 1 log(|ϵ 1 |/|ϵ 0 |),(10)where ϵ 0 is the dominant eigenvalue of T, and ϵ 1 is the second-largest eigenvalue, ensuring that |ϵ 1 | ̸ = |ϵ 0 |.In the top panel of Fig. 7, we show the saturation of EE with increasing χ in the Z - q AFM ⊕ Z 2 NM and the Z 2 NM phases, confirming that these phases are noncritical.",
    "On the contrary, in QLRO ⊕ Z 2 NM phase (or standard QLRO for J 2 /J 1 < 1/2, not shown), the EE shows critical scaling [12][13][14]:S = c 6 log ξ + b,(11)where c is the central charge for the corresponding conformal field theory (CFT) with b being a non-universal constant."
  ]
}